This paper presents an alternative layer to convolution layers in convolutional neural networks (CNNs) that reduces the complexity of convolutions by replacing it with binary decisions. This approach is related to computer vision (CV) and machine learning (LG) as it deals with CNNs and decision trees. The paper also discusses the backpropagation algorithm, which is a common optimization method used in artificial intelligence (AI) and neural networks (NE). Finally, the paper presents empirical results on multiple publicly available data sets, which is related to data science (DS). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CV and cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.DS.
